<li>
g++ is actually a script which calls gcc with the appropriate options in
order to compile C++. Standard suffixes for C++ source files are: <tt>.C</tt>,
<tt>.cc</tt>, <tt>.cxx</tt>, <tt>.cpp</tt>, or <tt>.c++</tt>.
</li>
<li>
I recommend using g++ like so:<br />
<tt class="cmd">g++ -Wall file1 [file2 [file3...]] -o output_file</tt>
</li>
</points>

